column1: Who will win the 2020 Arizona Democratic primary?

column6: ['US Politics', 'Elections and Referenda']

The RCP average is currently at +22.5 for Joseph R Biden [1]. Further, 538 predicts that Joseph R Biden is currently polling at 56.7% [2]. However, Arizona has recently closed 78 polling stations and blocked mail-in ballots in Maricopa county due to Coronavirus fears [3]. Further, Arizona is a closed primary state which limits the ability of GOP voters to conduct "Operation Chaos" voting that normally goes for Bernie Sanders [4].
